2. Implement fix per fix. Add tests as you go (TDD-able since each is a regression test for a real bug).
3. Run `pnpm --filter @ax/eventbus-postgres test`, `pnpm --filter @ax/session-postgres test`, `pnpm --filter @ax/database-postgres test` after each fix.
4. Final: `pnpm test` full repo green.
5. **One commit per fix** OR a single combined commit titled `fix(postgres-trio): production hardening (error handlers, reconnect chain, TOCTOU)` if they're tightly coupled. Use your judgment; the reviewer left three separate comments so three commits is also fine.

## Context

- Worktree: `/Users/vpulim/dev/ai/ax-next/.worktrees/week-7-9`. Branch `feat/week-7-9-k8s-deployment`.
- Five invariants in `CLAUDE.md` apply. Most relevant: I5 capability minimization (these fixes don't widen capabilities; they just prevent crashes).
- Existing tests use `@testcontainers/postgresql` ŌĆö the harness is well-established.

## Self-Review

